A chieftain and leader of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Chief Sir Marc Inyanagbo Wabara has called for continued support for the Buhari administration to enable it achieve its set goals and objectives. He stated that no leader, no matter how highly focused and determined, would be able to accomplish a mission without the active support of members of his team and the populace. In a statement released yesterday, Wabara reminded Nigerians that obedience to constituted authorities was critical in the pursuit of a better society, adding that every Nigerian should see the need in supporting President Muhammadu Buhari-led administration to achieve its lofty goals for the country. Wabara said so far, the federal government had embarked on massive infrastructural development across the country, ranging from roads, bridges, rail to airport terminals, adding that he was confident that the people of the South East have been excited with the ongoing construction of the second Niger Bridge, the reconstruction of the Enugu – Umuahia – Port Harcourt Express Way and completion of the renovation of the Enugu International Airport, among other projects in the region. He called on the various agencies of government to focus on complementing the efforts of the federal government in order to ensure that Nigerians enjoy more dividends of democracy.